markdown: <::A scatter plot titled "BLOOD PRESSURE (mm Hg)" on the y-axis versus "SALT INTAKE (g/day)" on the x-axis. The x-axis ranges from 0 to 28 in increments of 4. The y-axis ranges from 60 to 180 in increments of 10. The y-axis is divided into two sections: "Diastolic" (from 60 to approximately 100) and "Systolic" (from approximately 100 to 180). There are two sets of data points and corresponding regression lines: 1. **Systolic Blood Pressure**: Represented by filled circles. The regression line for systolic blood pressure is labeled "Y = 114 + 1.60X". 2. **Diastolic Blood Pressure**: Represented by open circles. The regression line for diastolic blood pressure is labeled "Y = 73.8 + 78 X". The legend indicates: - An open square represents "two values". - A filled square represents "two values". Data points are scattered around both regression lines, showing a general positive correlation between salt intake and both systolic and diastolic blood pressure. : chart::> Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/njnf0227
